<p><a href="/articles/semaglutide-weight-loss-guide">Semaglutide</a> changed the obesity treatment world. Tirzepatide raised the bar.</p>

<p>Developed by Eli Lilly, tirzepatide is the first <strong>dual GLP-1/GIP receptor agonist</strong> to receive FDA approval. It targets two incretin hormones instead of one, and the results speak for themselves: up to <strong>22.5% body weight loss</strong> in clinical trials.</p>

<p>It's sold as <strong>Mounjaro</strong> for type 2 diabetes and <strong>Zepbound</strong> for weight management. Both names, same molecule.</p>

<div class="d">
